# Fake News Detection

This project focuses on identifying whether a news article is real or fake using machine learning and basic NLP techniques.

Fake news detection is essentially a text classification problem, where the goal is to classify articles based on their content. ([Kaggle][1])

---

## What I did

* Cleaned and processed text data
* Converted text into numerical features (like TF-IDF)
* Trained models to classify news as real or fake
* Evaluated performance using standard metrics

---

## Dataset

* Collection of real and fake news articles
* Includes title, text, and labels
* Built for NLP classification tasks ([Kaggle][2])

---

## Approach

* Text preprocessing (stopwords, cleaning, etc.)
* Feature extraction
* Model training and evaluation

---

## Models used

* Logistic Regression
* Naive Bayes / other basic classifiers

---

## Key takeaway

Language patterns can help identify fake news, but context and meaning still make it a challenging problem.

